<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-96A39F98-3BEF-4415-A2B0-4683B4FCB10A" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-96A39F98-3BEF-4415-A2B0-4683B4FCB10A" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">How to use Teamviewer for Remote Assistance</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-3971E95F-7900-4495-B02B-0182D686A815"><p class="- topic/p ">The back office or help desk can use On Remote Service for several forms of assistance in the <ph class="- topic/ph " varid="productname">Colorado M-Series</ph>. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Tools</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-2E606B6C-6694-41AF-BCEA-AE6288619518" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to connect</title><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Use 
<xref href="https://prismaservice.cpp.canon" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://prismaservice.cpp.canon</xref> to login to PRISMAservice. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Search for your device: 
</p><fig id="GUID-258E6D20-6E77-48B5-A4BC-89598D26A6C3" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "> Search configurations</title><image href="GUID-35CD4F3D-ECED-42D4-98EA-B82CEABC8CDD-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-35CD4F3D-ECED-42D4-98EA-B82CEABC8CDD-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Click on the result row to open the device. 
</p></li></ol></section><section id="GUID-C6F5D82A-F632-438B-8744-791BB674167A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Off-site (support) procedure</title><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Log in to the ORS portal On Remote Service (https://prismaservice.cpp.canon). 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Using the product selector, search for your device and open the overview. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> In the opened overview, select [Repair] -&gt; [Remote assistance]. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Select the desired option "RDP" or "VPN" and click [Go]. See the table below for details. 
</p><table id="GUID-4A64023E-1552-4003-8013-82D898BDE8F0" class="- topic/table "><title class="- topic/title ">Selectable options </title><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="25*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="60*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Option 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Meaning 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Purpose 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">RDP 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remote Desktop Protocol 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">used for interacting with the printer’s local UI 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">VPN 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Virtual Private Network 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">used for gaining remote access to the printers (web) Settings editor 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><note id="GUID-EADE5AB6-4B24-4942-A169-69DFDD75A240" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">This selection and button are only usable when Remote Assistance is allowed by the customer. The ORS screen will look like the screenshot below 
</p></note><fig id="GUID-01669038-217E-482A-927A-D501EA1FA261" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A4FA5088-8645-4879-A6AF-26F1FA6FD2A9-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A4FA5088-8645-4879-A6AF-26F1FA6FD2A9-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> A message will pop up to wait, taking into account that the file downloaded (containing the login credentials) is only valid for a limited amount of time. 
</p><fig id="GUID-5AFE43CF-0A0E-4E7C-B9BD-AC34A3F24B24" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-86A38C59-7B3A-41C1-BFA4-10A1FFF8143B-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-86A38C59-7B3A-41C1-BFA4-10A1FFF8143B-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The file “remoteassistance.exe” will be downloaded. On completion of the download, open this by clicking on “Open file”. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Enter the password in the popup window and select “OK” (this password can be found in 
<xref keyref="PASSWORDS" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-12C05EB7-B241-4D9D-B2F7-676AF8025DB2.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text User Names & Passwords?>User Names &amp; Passwords</xref> ) 
</p><fig id="GUID-283285DB-EC96-4B4E-B1F7-911BD046B07B" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-954248C4-3F55-4454-9B20-969872247149-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-954248C4-3F55-4454-9B20-969872247149-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> A TeamViewer session starts and connects automatically to the control panel of the selected printer. 
</p><fig id="GUID-A275292A-1FCD-4185-B179-1B6FA54C54AC" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-E50DB218-0A95-4249-B01F-0CBBF7958128-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E50DB218-0A95-4249-B01F-0CBBF7958128-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Also a remote control screen will be shown. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7FB38808-91B8-4F31-A8F2-95BD31381F0A" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "> Remote view</title><image href="GUID-20481F28-CA78-4287-B4C7-38141FC2D29A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-20481F28-CA78-4287-B4C7-38141FC2D29A-low.png"/></fig></li></ol></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-DFD95E44-6FE2-4690-855D-446A64ABF90C.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>ORS: On Remote Service</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
